<h1>Community Medicine (PSM)<br>5 Marks Question & Answers</h1>

<h2>Family Planning & Maternal Health</h2>

<div class="qa">
<p class="q">Q1. What are different kinds of family planning devices available in the National Family Welfare Programme?</p>
<div class="a">
<ul>
<li>Barrier methods – Condoms (Nirodh)</li>
<li>IUCD – Cu-T 380A, Cu-T 375</li>
<li>Hormonal methods – OCPs (Mala-N, Mala-D), Centchroman</li>
<li>Injectable contraceptives – Antara</li>
<li>Permanent methods – Tubectomy, Vasectomy</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="qa">
<p class="q">Q2. What do you mean by ‘cafeteria approach’ under NFWP?</p>
<div class="a">
<ul>
<li>Provision of multiple contraceptive choices</li>
<li>Freedom to choose preferred method</li>
<li>Based on age, parity and health</li>
<li>Improves acceptability and compliance</li>
<li>Ensures informed decision-making</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="qa">
<p class="q">Q3. Who is an ideal candidate for Cu-T?</p>
<div class="a">
<ul>
<li>Married woman with at least one child</li>
<li>Wants spacing contraception</li>
<li>No PID or STI</li>
<li>Not pregnant</li>
<li>Regular menstrual cycles</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="qa">
<p class="q">Q4. Is it essential to know attitude of elderly regarding family planning?</p>
<div class="a">
<ul>
<li>Elders influence family decisions</li>
<li>Affects acceptance of methods</li>
<li>Cultural beliefs matter</li>
<li>Improves compliance</li>
<li>Prevents discontinuation</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="qa">
<p class="q">Q5. What is PNDT Act?</p>
<div class="a">
<ul>
<li>Pre-Natal Diagnostic Techniques Act</li>
<li>Prevents sex determination</li>
<li>Prevents female foeticide</li>
<li>Regulates diagnostic techniques</li>
<li>Punishable if violated</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="qa">
<p class="q">Q6. What are conventional contraceptives? What is an ideal contraceptive?</p>
<div class="a">
<b>Conventional:</b>
<ul>
<li>Condom</li>
<li>Diaphragm</li>
<li>Foams and jellies</li>
</ul>
<b>Ideal contraceptive:</b>
<ul>
<li>Effective</li>
<li>Safe</li>
<li>Reversible</li>
<li>Affordable</li>
<li>Acceptable</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="qa">
<p class="q">Q7. Enumerate high-risk pregnancy criteria.</p>
<div class="a">
<ul>
<li>Age &lt;18 or &gt;35 years</li>
<li>Parity ≥4</li>
<li>Previous obstetric complications</li>
<li>Anemia, PIH, diabetes</li>
<li>Multiple pregnancy</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="qa">
<p class="q">Q8. Minimum ANC visits and actions?</p>
<div class="a">
<ul>
<li>Minimum 4 visits</li>
<li>1st – Registration, TT, Hb</li>
<li>2nd – BP, weight, fundal height</li>
<li>3rd – IFA, danger signs</li>
<li>4th – Birth preparedness</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="qa">
<p class="q">Q9. Additional nutrients during pregnancy?</p>
<div class="a">
<ul>
<li>Calories +350 kcal/day</li>
<li>Protein +23 g/day</li>
<li>Iron and folic acid</li>
<li>Calcium</li>
<li>Vitamin supplementation</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="qa">
<p class="q">Q10. Drugs contraindicated in pregnancy?</p>
<div class="a">
<ul>
<li>Thalidomide</li>
<li>Isotretinoin</li>
<li>Warfarin</li>
<li>Tetracycline</li>
<li>Valproate</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<h2>Nutrition & Dietetics</h2>

<div class="qa">
<p class="q">Q18. Methods of assessing nutritional status?</p>
<div class="a">
<ul>
<li>Anthropometry</li>
<li>Clinical examination</li>
<li>Biochemical tests</li>
<li>Dietary assessment</li>
<li>Functional tests</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="qa">
<p class="q">Q21. Dietary advice for a 3-year-old child with Vitamin-A deficiency?</p>
<div class="a">
<ul>
<li>Green leafy vegetables</li>
<li>Yellow fruits and vegetables</li>
<li>Milk and butter</li>
<li>Egg yolk and liver</li>
<li>Vitamin-A supplementation</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<h2>Under-Five & Adolescent Health</h2>

<div class="qa">
<p class="q">Q30. Who is an adolescent?</p>
<div class="a">
<ul>
<li>Age group 10–19 years</li>
<li>WHO definition</li>
<li>Transitional phase</li>
<li>Rapid growth period</li>
<li>Psychosocial changes</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="qa">
<p class="q">Q36. Components of newborn care?</p>
<div class="a">
<ul>
<li>Thermal care</li>
<li>Early breastfeeding</li>
<li>Cord care</li>
<li>Immunization</li>
<li>Infection prevention</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<h2>Environment, Hygiene & Sanitation</h2>

<div class="qa">
<p class="q">Q42. Criteria for overcrowding?</p>
<div class="a">
<ul>
<li>Floor space</li>
<li>Persons per room</li>
<li>Cubic space</li>
<li>Ventilation</li>
<li>Sleeping arrangement</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<div class="qa">
<p class="q">Q44. Mosquito-borne diseases?</p>
<div class="a">
<ul>
<li>Malaria</li>
<li>Dengue</li>
<li>Chikungunya</li>
<li>Zika</li>
<li>Filariasis</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<h2>Immunization</h2>

<div class="qa">
<p class="q">Q65. National Immunization Schedule?</p>
<div class="a">
<ul>
<li>BCG</li>
<li>OPV</li>
<li>Pentavalent</li>
<li>Measles/MR</li>
<li>TT/Td</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

<h2>Socio-Economics & Sociology</h2>

<div class="qa">
<p class="q">Q85. Enumerate functions of family.</p>
<div class="a">
<ul>
<li>Reproduction</li>
<li>Socialization</li>
<li>Economic support</li>
<li>Emotional support</li>
<li>Health care</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>

